\v 4 —\w every|strong="G3956"\w* \w house|strong="G3624"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w built|strong="G2680"\w* \w by|strong="G5259"\w* \w someone|strong="G5100"\w*, \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w He|strong="G1161"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w built|strong="G2680"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w things|strong="G3956"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*—
\v 5 \w also|strong="G2532"\w*, \w Moses|strong="G3475"\w* \w was|strong="G3588"\w* \w indeed|strong="G2532"\w* \w faithful|strong="G4103"\w* \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w servant|strong="G2324"\w* \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w all|strong="G3650"\w* \w His|strong="G1519"\w* \w house|strong="G3624"\w*, providing evidence \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w things|strong="G3588"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w would|strong="G2532"\w* later \w be|strong="G2532"\w* \w spoken|strong="G2980"\w*,\f + \fr 3:5 \ft A curious statement—he provided evidence before it was called for, as it were. Of course Moses is referred to many times in the Scriptures written after his day.\f*
\v 6 \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w* faithful \w as|strong="G5613"\w* \w a|strong="G5613"\w* \w Son|strong="G5207"\w* \w over|strong="G1909"\w* \w His|strong="G1909"\w* \w house|strong="G3624"\w*, \w whose|strong="G3739"\w* \w house|strong="G3624"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* \w we|strong="G2249"\w*, \w if|strong="G1437"\w*, \w that|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G1510"\w*, \w we|strong="G2249"\w* \w hold|strong="G2722"\w* \w fast|strong="G2722"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w confidence|strong="G3954"\w*, \w even|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w boast|strong="G2745"\w*,\f + \fr 3:6 \ft I suppose that a sincere boasting is an exaggerated form of confidence.\f* \w of|strong="G5207"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Hope|strong="G1680"\w*\f + \fr 3:6 \ft I take it that the Hope has to do with eternal life. To still be part of the “house” at the end, one must never give up “the confidence”.\f* firm \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w end|strong="G5056"\w*.\f + \fr 3:6 \ft Less than 1% of the Greek manuscripts, of objectively inferior quality, omit “firm to the end” (as in NIV, LB, TEV, etc.).\f*
