\q2 ‘\w As|strong="G5613"\w* \w if|strong="G1487"\w* \w they|strong="G3588"\w* \w will|strong="G1473"\w* \w ever|strong="G1519"\w* \w enter|strong="G1525"\w* \w my|strong="G1722"\w* \w rest|strong="G2663"\w*!’ ”\f + \fr 3:11 \ft See Psalm 95:7-11.\f*
\m 
\v 12 —\w take|strong="G2316"\w* care, brothers, \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w there|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G1510"\w* \w be|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G1722"\w* \w malignant|strong="G4190"\w* \w heart|strong="G2588"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* unbelief \w in|strong="G1722"\w* \w any|strong="G5100"\w* \w of|strong="G2316"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w*, \w so|strong="G3379"\w* \w as|strong="G1722"\w* \w to|strong="G1722"\w* go away \w from|strong="G3588"\w*\f + \fr 3:12 \ft Notice the direction. The term ‘malignant’ implies Satanic influence.\f* \w the|strong="G1722"\w* \w living|strong="G2198"\w* \w God|strong="G2316"\w*;
\v 13 rather, \w exhort|strong="G3870"\w* \w yourselves|strong="G1438"\w*\f + \fr 3:13 \ft The pronoun here is reflexive, not reciprocal, but being plural probably includes both ideas—each one should exhort himself, but we should also exhort each other.\f* \w every|strong="G2596"\w* \w day|strong="G2250"\w*, \w while|strong="G2250"\w* \w it|strong="G3739"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* \w called|strong="G2564"\w* ‘\w today|strong="G4594"\w*’, \w so|strong="G2443"\w* \w that|strong="G2443"\w* \w none|strong="G3361"\w* \w of|strong="G1537"\w* \w you|strong="G5210"\w* \w be|strong="G3361"\w* \w hardened|strong="G4645"\w* \w through|strong="G2596"\w* sin's deceitfulness.
\v 14 \w For|strong="G1063"\w* \w we|strong="G1437"\w* \w have|strong="G1096"\w* \w become|strong="G1096"\w* associates \w of|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w Christ|strong="G5547"\w*, \w if|strong="G1437"\w*, \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w*, \w we|strong="G1437"\w* \w hold|strong="G2722"\w* \w fast|strong="G2722"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* beginning \w of|strong="G3588"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* Endeavor\f + \fr 3:14 \ft I take it that the Christian life or walk with God is called “the Endeavor” (much like ‘the Way’); people usually start with confidence and enthusiasm, but frequently slow down as the going gets rough.\f* firm \w to|strong="G1096"\w* \w the|strong="G3588"\w* \w end|strong="G5056"\w*,
