\v 2 Really, \w because|strong="G1063"\w* \w we|strong="G1063"\w* \w are|strong="G1510"\w* continually hearing \w Good|strong="G2097"\w* \w News|strong="G2097"\w*\f + \fr 4:2 \ft Strictly speaking it should be “we are continually being good-newsed/evangelized”, but to try to make a verb out of ‘good news’ is awkward; on the other hand ‘evangelize’ has the connotation of preaching the Gospel to an unbeliever, which is not the point here. I take the “Good News” here to be God's Truth, on any and all topics.\f* \w just|strong="G2509"\w* \w like|strong="G2509"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w did|strong="G2532"\w*, \w but|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w word|strong="G3056"\w* \w that|strong="G3588"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* heard \w did|strong="G2532"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* \w profit|strong="G5623"\w* \w them|strong="G3588"\w*, \w since|strong="G1063"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w not|strong="G3756"\w* intimately \w united|strong="G4786"\w* \w with|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w faith|strong="G4102"\w* \w of|strong="G3056"\w* \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* obeyed.
