\v 4 \w Because|strong="G1063"\w*, \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w is|strong="G3588"\w* impossible \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w bring|strong="G5461"\w* back \w into|strong="G1096"\w* repentance \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* once \w for|strong="G1063"\w* \w all|strong="G2532"\w* \w enlightened|strong="G5461"\w*, \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w have|strong="G2532"\w* partaken\f + \fr 6:4 \ft The verb here—whether ‘to taste’, ‘to partake’, ‘to obtain’ or ‘to come to know’—has to do with \nd experience\nd*.\f* \w of|strong="G4151"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w heavenly|strong="G2032"\w* \w gift|strong="G1431"\w* \w and|strong="G2532"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w made|strong="G1096"\w* sharers \w in|strong="G2532"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w Holy|strong="G4151"\w* \w Spirit|strong="G4151"\w*,\f + \fr 6:4 \ft It seems clear enough that the reference is to people who have the Holy Spirit.\f*
